radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring 10 mm with a proximal obstructing appendicolith. No associated drainable fluid collection or extraluminal gas. Trace amount of free fluid within the pelvis, which may be physiologic and/or reactive. Minimal bibasilar atelectasis. No free fluid, free air, or lymphadenopathy within the abdomen. Normal imaging of the heart, liver, kidneys, stomach, and bowel.
